<html>
<head>
  <meta charset="utf-8" />
  <title>AYRA ERP System Requirements Specification</title>
  <style>
    body { font-family: Calibri, Arial, sans-serif; margin: 36px; color: #1f2937; line-height: 1.5; }
    h1, h2, h3 { color: #0f172a; }
    h1 { text-align: center; margin-bottom: 8px; }
    .subtitle { text-align: center; color: #475569; margin-bottom: 28px; }
    table { border-collapse: collapse; width: 100%; margin: 14px 0 24px; }
    th, td { border: 1px solid #cbd5e1; padding: 8px 10px; text-align: left; vertical-align: top; }
    th { background: #e2e8f0; }
    ul { margin-top: 6px; }
    .section { margin-top: 26px; }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <h1>System Requirements Specification</h1>
  <p class="subtitle">Project: AYRA ERP Portal</p>

  <div class="section">
    <h2>1. Introduction</h2>
    <p>
      AYRA ERP is a web-based academic enterprise resource planning system designed to support students,
      teachers, academic office staff, and communication teams. The system centralizes student records,
      subject and class management, academic approvals, calendar events, leave processing, and email alert
      communication through role-based dashboards.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    <h2>2. Project Objective</h2>
    <p>
      The objective of the AYRA ERP project is to provide a unified university management platform that
      improves information access, academic coordination, student monitoring, and communication efficiency.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    <h2>3. Scope of the System</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Student profile, progress, timetable, advisory, leave, and calendar access</li>
      <li>Teacher-side management of students, subjects, classes, advisories, progress, and alerts</li>
      <li>Academic office management of teachers, curriculum plans, timetables, records, approvals, and alerts</li>
      <li>Communication management for announcements, campaigns, event publishing, and response tracking</li>
      <li>Email alert delivery to all students or selected student email groups</li>
      <li>MongoDB-based persistence for operational records and alert history</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    <h2>4. Users and Roles</h2>
    <table>
      <tr>
        <th>Role</th>
        <th>Main Responsibilities</th>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Student</td>
        <td>View profile, progress, classes, advisories, calendar, and apply for leave</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Teacher</td>
        <td>Manage students, subjects, classes, progress, advisories, and send alerts</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Academic Office</td>
        <td>Manage teachers, curriculum, approvals, records, student registry, leave monitoring, and alerts</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Communication Team</td>
        <td>Manage announcements, campaigns, events, and response tracking</td>
      </tr>
    </table>
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    <h2>5. Functional Requirements</h2>

    <h3>5.1 Authentication and Access Control</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>The system shall provide login functionality for all supported user roles.</li>
      <li>The system shall provide tenant-based routing and role-based dashboard access.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>5.2 Student Module</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>The system shall display student profile information, department, semester, section, and status.</li>
      <li>The system shall display semester progress, attendance, marks, and remarks.</li>
      <li>The system shall allow students to submit leave requests.</li>
      <li>The system shall allow students to view advisories and calendar events.</li>
      <li>The system shall support student profile photo upload and removal.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>5.3 Teacher Module</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>The system shall allow teachers to create, update, and delete student records.</li>
      <li>The system shall store student email addresses for communication.</li>
      <li>The system shall allow teachers to manage subject lists and class schedules.</li>
      <li>The system shall allow teachers to publish advisories.</li>
      <li>The system shall allow teachers to update student marks, attendance, and remarks.</li>
      <li>The system shall allow teachers to review and decide leave applications.</li>
      <li>The system shall allow teachers to send email alerts to all students or selected student groups.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>5.4 Academic Office Module</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>The system shall allow academic office staff to create and manage teacher accounts.</li>
      <li>The system shall allow academic office staff to manage curriculum plans and timetables.</li>
      <li>The system shall allow academic office staff to manage academic approvals and records.</li>
      <li>The system shall allow academic office staff to monitor leave requests.</li>
      <li>The system shall allow academic office staff to send and review student alert messages.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>5.5 Communication Module</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>The system shall allow communication users to manage announcements.</li>
      <li>The system shall allow communication users to manage campaigns and event records.</li>
      <li>The system shall allow communication users to maintain response tracking data.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>5.6 Alert and Email Module</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>The system shall send alert emails using Nodemailer through a configured Gmail account.</li>
      <li>The system shall support audiences based on all students, department, semester, section, or specific student emails.</li>
      <li>The system shall validate student email targets against registered approved student records.</li>
      <li>The system shall store alert history including audience, recipient count, status, and timestamps.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    <h2>6. Non-Functional Requirements</h2>
    <table>
      <tr>
        <th>Category</th>
        <th>Requirement</th>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Usability</td>
        <td>The system shall provide a modern responsive dashboard UI for desktop and mobile usage.</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Performance</td>
        <td>The system shall support normal academic ERP operations with quick CRUD response for typical college-scale usage.</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Reliability</td>
        <td>The system shall preserve academic and communication data in MongoDB with route-level validation.</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Security</td>
        <td>The system shall use role-based access flow and environment variables for mail and database configuration.</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Maintainability</td>
        <td>The system shall follow modular frontend and backend structure for easier extension.</td>
      </tr>
    </table>
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    <h2>7. Software Requirements</h2>
    <table>
      <tr>
        <th>Component</th>
        <th>Requirement</th>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Operating System</td>
        <td>Windows 10/11, Linux, or macOS</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Frontend</td>
        <td>React 18, Vite 5, React Router DOM 6, Material UI 5, Tailwind CSS 3</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Backend</td>
        <td>Node.js, Express 4, Mongoose 8, Nodemailer 6</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Database</td>
        <td>MongoDB Community or MongoDB Atlas</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Development Tools</td>
        <td>VS Code, npm, Nodemon, Git</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Browser Support</td>
        <td>Google Chrome, Microsoft Edge, Mozilla Firefox</td>
      </tr>
    </table>
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    <h2>8. Hardware Requirements</h2>
    <table>
      <tr>
        <th>Item</th>
        <th>Minimum Requirement</th>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Processor</td>
        <td>Intel Core i3 / AMD equivalent or above</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>RAM</td>
        <td>4 GB minimum, 8 GB recommended</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Storage</td>
        <td>2 GB free disk space minimum</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Internet</td>
        <td>Required for email alert delivery and cloud deployment</td>
      </tr>
    </table>
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    <h2>9. Database Requirements</h2>
    <p>The system uses MongoDB collections for the following major entities:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Users</li>
      <li>Students</li>
      <li>Teacher Subjects</li>
      <li>Class Schedules</li>
      <li>Advisories</li>
      <li>Student Progress</li>
      <li>Leave Requests</li>
      <li>Curriculum Plans</li>
      <li>Timetables</li>
      <li>Academic Approvals</li>
      <li>Academic Records</li>
      <li>Announcements</li>
      <li>Campaigns</li>
      <li>Calendar Events</li>
      <li>Response Tracking</li>
      <li>Teacher and Academic Alerts</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    <h2>10. Deployment Requirements</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Frontend may be deployed on Vercel.</li>
      <li>Backend may be deployed on Render or Railway.</li>
      <li>Cloud deployment requires a hosted MongoDB URI; localhost MongoDB is only for local development.</li>
      <li>Environment variables required: MONGODB_URI, DEFAULT_TENANT, MAIL_ALERT_EMAIL, MAIL_ALERT_APP_PASSWORD, MAIL_ALERT_FROM_NAME, and frontend API base URL.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    <h2>11. Assumptions and Constraints</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>The system assumes valid student email addresses are entered while creating student records.</li>
      <li>The system assumes Gmail app password configuration for email alert delivery.</li>
      <li>The current project uses a single tenant example, with tenant-ready routing for extension.</li>
      <li>The project currently focuses on ERP operations and not on online payment gateway integration.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    <h2>12. Conclusion</h2>
    <p>
      AYRA ERP is a modular academic ERP solution that integrates student management, academic administration,
      timetable planning, communication workflows, and role-based email alerts into one centralized platform.
      The project is suitable for academic institutions seeking a lightweight but extensible ERP foundation.
    </p>
  </div>
</body>
</html>
